{"uid":"44c69f0139fd032b","name":"test_soft_deleted_customer_is_still_returned_by_api","fullName":"tests.customers.api.test_soft_deleted_customer_handling#test_soft_deleted_customer_is_still_returned_by_api","historyId":"86e8fa1e5dc3e31591f93d5ad31bd8fd","time":{"start":1784153834189,"stop":1784153834596,"duration":407},"description":"\nVerify WooCommerce soft-delete behavior.\n\nSoft-deleting a customers in the database (user_status = 1):\n    - keeps the customers record in the database\n    - does NOT remove the customers from the WooCommerce API response\n\nThis test documents the default WooCommerce behavior.\n\nTest flow:\n    1. Create a customers via fixture\n    2. Soft-delete the customers in DB (user_status = 1)\n    3. Confirm DB reflects the soft deletion\n    4. Verify API still returns the customers\n\nNote:\n    WooCommerce uses \"soft delete_it.py\" via status flags (e.g., user_status, post_status='trash').\n    However, the core REST API does not automatically exclude such entities unless customized.\n\n","descriptionHtml":"<p>Verify WooCommerce soft-delete behavior.</p>\n<p>Soft-deleting a customers in the database (user_status = 1):<br />\n- keeps the customers record in the database<br />\n- does NOT remove the customers from the WooCommerce API response</p>\n<p>This test documents the default WooCommerce behavior.</p>\n<p>Test flow:<br />\n1. Create a customers via fixture<br />\n2. Soft-delete the customers in DB (user_status = 1)<br />\n3. Confirm DB reflects the soft deletion<br />\n4. Verify API still returns the customers</p>\n<p>Note:<br />\nWooCommerce uses &quot;soft delete_it.py&quot; via status flags (e.g., user_status, post_status='trash').<br />\nHowever, the core REST API does not automatically exclude such entities unless customized.</p>\n","status":"passed","flaky":false,"newFailed":false,"newBroken":false,"newPassed":false,"retriesCount":0,"retriesStatusChange":false,"beforeStages":[{"name":"_session_faker","time":{"start":17841